                <h1>Understanding ERLC: Background & Significance</h1>
                <p>ERLC, or the Ethics and Religious Liberty Commission, serves as the public policy arm of the Southern Baptist Convention. It aims to advocate for religious liberty, morality, and justice in society. Focused on issues like family, life, and human rights, ERLC engages in cultural conversations, providing resources and guidance for believers.</p>
